12, Nam, etc. The thought is that, under whichever of the possible forms of government you live, politieal sagacity implies a study of the character of the sovereign power„

13. delecta exiis, etc. Such a govem- ment was the ideal of Polybius (6. 3, 7), and of Cicero, who says ‘ quartum quod- dam genus maxime probandum censeo quod ex his quae prima dixi moderatum et permixtum tribus' (de Rep, 1. 29, 45 : cp· also 35, 54³ 45, 693 2· 23, 41). Polybius further (6. 11, 6) finds the nearest realisation of such an ideal in the Roman constitution at his time.
